### 1) Bootstrap first admin (development only)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/bootstrap-admin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "AdminPass123!"
}

### 2) Login as admin (OAuth2 form)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin&password=AdminPass123!

### 3) Seed default strategies/symbols
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin-api/seed
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>

### 4) List strategies
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin-api/strategies
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>

### 5) List symbols
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin-api/symbols
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>

### 6) Scan an assignment and persist its signal snapshot
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/signals/assignments/1/scan
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "htf_limit": 120,
  "ltf_limit": 240
}

### 7) List persisted signal history for an assignment with pagination/date filters
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/signals/assignments/1/history?offset=0&limit=20&created_from=2026-03-10T00:00:00Z&created_to=2026-03-12T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>

### 8) Get frontend-ready overlay payload for an assignment
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/signals/assignments/1/overlay?offset=0&limit=20&created_from=2026-03-10T00:00:00Z&created_to=2026-03-12T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>

### 9) Admin list of signal events with filters and pagination
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin-api/signal-events?symbol_id=1&strategy_id=1&signal_status=READY&trigger=EXECUTE&offset=0&limit=50&created_from=2026-03-10T00:00:00Z&created_to=2026-03-12T23:59:59Z
Authorization: Bearer <PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>
